s a sauce made with basil, pine nuts, Parmesan and olive oil. While pesto is a generic term given to any sauce made by pounding ingredients, ‘Genovese pesto’ remains the most popular pesto in Italy as well as being enjoyed around the world. In our take on the classic dish <i>trenette al pesto<\/i>, we’ve swapped traditional trenette pasta for fusilli, a spiral pasta shape that catches the sauce well.","To make this recipe suitable for vegetarians, substitute the Parmesan and pecorino for vegetarian hard cheeses."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","6 portions"]}